 do last entered a recording studio. Once known as the &ldquo\;Queen of Fee
 ling\,&rdquo\; her voice was celebrated throughout Cuba&mdash\;until she v
 anished from the spotlight. But when an ambitious young record producer br
 ings her a rare opportunity\, the elusive diva must finally reckon with he
 r past.<br /><br />Hailed as a "jaw-dropping\, soul-stirring must see" (Th
 e Washington Post)\, the Tony&reg\; and Grammy&reg\; Award-winning <em>Bue
 na Vista Social Club</em>&nbsp\;is a journey through music and memory into
  the beating heart of Havana. A world-class company brings the story of th
 e iconic album to thrilling life in this tale of big dreams\, second chanc
 es\, and music that needs no translation.</p>
LOCATION:Gerald Schoenfeld Theatre\, 236 West 45th Street\, New York NY 10
 036
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Buena Vista Social Club
DTSTART:20260512T230000Z
DTEND:20260513T011000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T185141Z
